	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Dec 3rd 6:16 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=96654><span id= >dubyprime</span></a><br><span id=notbold>32 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.13]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This argument has been taking place since the dawning of Norrath, and it's REALLY starting to grate on my nerves.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, as far as game mechanics, no one excels at archery more than a ranger.  Rangers are the true archers.  However. . .<br><br>What 99.9% of the population of Norrath is forgetting is that EverQuest is a ROLE PLAYING game.  It's not Final Fantasy, where you endeavor for the weapon with the highest stats.  It's an ongoing fantasy adventure where you are supposed to &quot;roleplay&quot; your character.  Which is the reason not all bows are &quot;ranger only.&quot;  Think about it.  How many people ever played D&amp;D?  Were bows limited to rangers only?  How about movies?  Would you classify Robin Hood as a ranger?  Maybe some would, but he seems awfully &quot;roguish&quot; to me!  So people who want to roleplay their characters as archers shouldn't be able to strive for these nicer bows simply because they can't match the damage a ranger can do with it?  That's just numbers, people.  Numbers aren't what makes a true RPG fun.  But too many people have lost sight of that.<br><br>Don't get me wrong. . . if I was in a group that had a ranger in it when a nice bow dropped, I'd gladly give it up to him because it would benefit the group.  But don't flame non-rangers who actually go and seek out these fantastic weapons!  Perhaps he's an elf from Kelethin who was training as a ranger, yet was unable to complete his training because his father was killed and he was left to fend for himself as a pickpocket.  <br><br>Roleplaying, people.  That's what it's all about.<br><br>-Rannin Seawolfe<br>Lvl 55 Thief and ARCHER!!<br>Morell Thule<br><br>&quot;Everybody wants to go to Heaven. . . but nobody wants to die.&quot;<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Dec  3 17:54:35 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
